specialcase.p:
When n=1, we just get \R back: \R^1=\R.  Geometrically, this is the number line.

    \begin{tikzpicture}
      \draw [<->, thick] (-3.5,0) -- (3.5,0);
      \foreach \x in {-3,...,3}
         \draw[thin] (\x,-.1) -- (\x,0.1) node[anchor=south] {$\x$};
    \end{tikzpicture}

statement.p:
For our purposes, a line is a ray that is straight and infinite in both directions.

  \begin{tikzpicture}[scale=1]
    \draw[grid lines] (-2,-2) grid (2,2);
    \draw[->] (-2,0) -- (2,0);
    \draw[->] (0,-2) -- (0,2);
